reviews.text: Some of the best pizza in the area. Both the white sauce and the red sauce offer completely different experiences! You don't want to skip either. Although the Mushroom is an all time favorite, all the pizzas we've tried have been great!!

It's awesome they'll make a half and half pizza. Had a half sausage, half bacon and fig jam and it was as good as it gets. The pistachio gelato hit the perfect pistachio notes and wasn't overly sweet. Really happy to have found this place while in Lacrosse.

Edit. I went back for lunch and tried a few more slices. Got hot honey pepperoni and burrata and they were also fantastic.

The BEST Pizza I have ever had! I‚Äôm not a fan of Pizzas but I could eat any of their pizza slices all day! The flavors are unique and delicious! They also use organic and quality ingredients. The people, especially Spencer, are so passionate about their craft and are very friendly and accommodating! Don‚Äôt forget to try the yummy Gelato as well! Food + Service = Awesome Experience!

If you're a pizza lover, do yourself a favor and check this place out. It‚Äôs easily one of the best pizza places in downtown.
Can‚Äôt wait to come back and try more from their menu!
Tried their bacon with fig jam along with garlic cream just mind-blowing. Combination is limited but hopefully they'll bring more options.

Able to mix and match halves of pizzas.  We had a 1/2 hot honey pepperoni, 1/2 sausage and giardiniera.  The texture of the crust on these pizzas was perfect.  The the bits of fresh basil on the pepperoni half made just a really nice accent to the slice.  It is an order at the counter type place (they also sell by the slice), they'll bring your pizza to your table, and there is a little service area to grab paper plates and napkins.

recentReviews.text: Fantastic food & service!!  Hot honey pizza never disappoints!!
This place hits just right! I wish they were open a little later,  but I really enjoy it! I‚Äôll be back

Have picked up slices for lunch twice. Im a traditionalist, so I didnt enjoy the white sauce pizzas. Had sausage and onion both times as well Once was OK as the crust was a little burnt in my opinion. Second time was damn tasty. Will probably just order my own pie moving forward. Sandwiches looked solid.

The staff were very friendly. The pizza is good, but could be improved upon. We had pepporoni and mushroom. I thought the toppings a bit skimpy. The pepporoni was the minis, like sold at stores. It was salty and just not as good as full large slices. The mushrooms were almost nonexistent and very skimpy on the cheese. For the price, I'd expect a bit more. Crust was chewy, slightly charred on bottom, which I like some char, but the crust lacked a crunch. I would rate this pizzeria higher than a chain, but not as good as a New York pizza.

detailedReviews.text: Stopped in for pizza with 2 friends. Had the spicy vodka with pepperoni & sausage, half a white fig pizza and half burrata. Everything was great; spicy, sweet and savory. detailedReviews.author: Stacia Nordin
detailedReviews.text:
Pizzeria Dolorosa did NOT disappoint, very opposite to that - it was superbly superb.

I got a white garlic sauce topped with mushrooms and caramelized onion pizza and spent each bite guessing the ingredients. Seemed like a hint of blue cheese. Whatever it was - wow.

Kristof raved about his red sauce meat pizza that also had caramelized onion.

Both of us raved about the crust, crispy with a bit of crunch from cornmeal - very East Coast (my original home) - then a thin soft tasty crust near spicy, savoury toppings.

They gave us a hot pepper powder that was hard to figure out as well. A bit smoky, a bit chipotle, not hot, but spicy nice. I loaded my takeaways with it.

I had a Paul Busey cocktail with grapefruit juice that also had something spicy and salty.

We like when our taste buds dance!
